            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.22.3"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">3</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Beatrice, Nebraska
                        February 18, 1948
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Friend,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>You owe me a letter, I believe. It is rather difficult to recover from the shock of the first one. I liked your Christmas poem very much.</p> 
                
                <p>When looking through some personal affects<sic>effects</sic> this morning, I suddenly came upon the enclosed picture. This was taken in St. Louis. As I look at this picture, I think how marvelous it is that you and yoru wife can be so gifted and yet such honest to God human beings who keep their feet on the ground.</p> 
                
                <p>You said in your letter that you were seven grandfathers. Can that be true? Look at the enclosed picture and you will understand my question.</p>
                
                <p>Mrs. Neihardt, do you remember the kitty that was so sick, and you were concerned about how the youngest would take it, if the kitty were dead when we returned home: Remem-ber how she climbed out of the car, walked over to the kitty, coolly looked it over, then turned to you and said, "Well, it's deader than a door-nail!" Mrs. Munson often gets a good laugh out of that one.</p>
                
                <p>When we have time for memories, some of the brightest and most inspiring are those of the visits with you folks. Perhaps if we live right, we will have the pleasure of seeing you again.</p>
                
                <p>A letter would make us very happy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    <signed>H.<unclear>S.</unclear> Munson</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
